    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-09-27T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-09-27T13:00:00-05:00" n="658"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d658">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">760F.62/1168: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Czechoslovakia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Carr</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Praha</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-09-27T19:00:00+01:00"
                            >September 27, 1938—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received September 27—3:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>248. From Military Attaché. Local reaction to Hitler’s speech very bad but
                    considerable encouragement at very apparent sweep of feeling for this country in
                    England and France. G–2<note n="88" xml:id="d658fn88">Army Intelligence.</note>
                    confirms my last estimate of number of men under arms. Same source reports
                    maximum some eight German divisions in general area Linaz, Vienna, <pb
                        facs="0690" n="682" xml:id="pg_682"/> which together with smaller
                    concentrations north and west previously reported may mean main effort
                    contemplated northeast through south Moravian gate and secondary efforts south
                    and east on Praha.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Carr</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
